def data_research(dataset):
    
    
    #  5    .
    display(dataset.head())
    display(dataset.tail())
    print()
    
    
    #    .
    display(HTML('<h3>   </h3><br>'))
    print(dataset.info())
    
    
    #    .
    display(HTML('<h3> </h3><br>'))
    print(dataset.columns)
    
    
    #      .
    display(HTML('<br><h3>   </h3><br>'))
    
    if data.index.is_monotonic == True:
        print('    ')
    
    else:
        print('    ')
 

    #      .
    display(HTML('<br><h3>    </h3><br>'))
    
    if dataset.isna().sum().any():

        display(HTML(
            f'<b>    : </b>'\
            f'{dataset.isna().sum().sum()} '\
            f'({round((dataset.isna().sum().sum() / (dataset.shape[0] * dataset.shape[1]) * 100), 1)}%)<br>')
               )
        
        display(HTML(
            f'<b>,     : </b>'\
            f'{dataset[dataset.columns].isna().any(axis=1).sum()} '\
            f'({round((dataset[dataset.columns].isna().any(axis=1).sum() / dataset.shape[0] * 100), 1)}%)<br>')
               )
               
        display(HTML('<b>    : </b>'))
        display(pd.DataFrame({
            'count': dataset.isna().sum(),
            '%': dataset.isna().mean() * 100
            }).style.set_precision(1).background_gradient('coolwarm'))
    
    else:
        print(' ')
    
    
    #    .
    display(HTML('<br><h3>   </h3><br>'))
    
    if dataset.duplicated().sum() != 0:

        print(f': {dataset.duplicated().sum()} '
              f'({(dataset.duplicated().sum() / dataset.shape[0]):.2%} '\
              f'  )')
        
    else:
        print('  ')
    

    #    .
    display(HTML('<br><h3>   </h3><br>'))    
        
    for column in dataset.columns:
        display(HTML(f'<b>    "{column}": </b>'\
                     f'{len(dataset[column].unique())}'))
            
        print(dataset.sort_values(by=column)[column].unique())
   
    
    
    if len(dataset.columns) != 0:

        #     .
        display(HTML('<br><h3> </h3>'))
        display(dataset.describe())
        
        
        #     .
        display(HTML(
            '<br><h3>    </h3><br>'
        ))
        num_plots = len(dataset.columns)
        num_rows = (num_plots + 1) // 2

        #    .
        fig, axes = plt.subplots(num_rows, 2, figsize=(14, 5 * num_rows))

        #     1, 
        #  axes   .
        if num_rows == 1:
            axes = np.expand_dims(axes, axis=0)        
        
        #  .
        for i, column in enumerate(dataset.columns):
            row = i // 2
            col = i % 2
            sns.histplot(data=dataset, x=column, bins=20, ax=axes[row, col])
            axes[row, col].grid(True)
            axes[row, col].set_title(
                f'   {column}'
            )
            axes[row, col].set_xlabel(column)
            axes[row, col].set_ylabel(' ')
            axes[row, col].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=90)

        #    , 
        #    .
        if num_plots % 2 != 0:
            fig.delaxes(axes[-1, -1])

        #  .
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()
   
    else:
        pass

#        .
def make_features(data_new):
    #   
    data_new = data.copy()
    data_new['hour'] = data_new.index.hour
    data_new['day'] = data_new.index.day
    data_new['dayofweek'] = data_new.index.dayofweek
    
    interval = 24
    interval_count = 7
    
    #         1  24 .
    for lag in range(1, interval + 1):
        data_new['lag_{}'.format(lag)] = data_new['num_orders'].shift(lag)
    
    #         7 .
    for i in range(1, interval_count):
        lag = interval + interval * i
        data_new['lag_{}'.format(lag)] = data_new['num_orders'].shift(lag)

    #   
    data_new['rolling_mean'] = data_new['num_orders'].shift().rolling(
        window=interval
    ).mean() 
    
    return data_new

   model_results  ,        .











In [39]:



     


#    ,  
#     .
def model_results(model, model_name, 
                  X_train, y_train, 
                  X_val, y_val, 
                  results):
    
    #     .
    start_time = time.time()
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    train_time = time.time() - start_time

    #      .
    start_time = time.time()
    val_pred = model.predict(X_val)
    pred_time = time.time() - start_time

    #   RMSE    .
    rmse = mean_squared_error(y_val, val_pred, squared=False)

    #  .
    results = results.append(
        {'Model': model_name, 
         'Training Time': train_time, 
         'Prediction Time': pred_time,
         'RMSE': rmse}, 
        ignore_index=True)
    
    return model, results
